<h1>Data Domain Details</h1>
<table>
  <th>Column</th>
  <th>Value</th>
  <th>Description</th>
  <tr>
    <td>Name</td>
    <td><%= @data_domain.name %></td>
    <td>
      The &quot;Name&quot is used internally and cannot be changed.
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Code</td>
    <td><%= Label_TextBox_Switch("data_domain", @data_domain, "code") %></td>
    <td>
      The &quot;Code&quot will be exported and distributed to other systems. Therefore, this value will be used by other systems to identify this value.
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Short Name</td>
    <td><%= Label_TextBox_Switch("data_domain", @data_domain, "short_name") %></td>
    <td>
      The &quot;Short Name&quot will be used on reports and will be the shorthand method of refering to this data domain.
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td>Description</td>
    <td><%= Label_TextBox_Switch("data_domain", @data_domain, "description") %></td>
    <td>
      The &quot;Description&quot can be utilised to provide a greater understanding of the data domain being constructed. This can be used for tooltips and other documentation in order to provide complete clarity.
    </td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <th colspan="3">Child Data Sub Domains</td>
  </tr>
  <% @data_domain.data_sub_domain_data_elements.each do |data_sub_domain| %>
  <tr>
    <td colspan="3"><%= LinkDataSheet(data_sub_domain, "friendly_name", { :data_sheet => data_sub_domain.name, :override_label => data_sub_domain.friendly_name }) %></td>
  </tr>
  <% end %>
      
</table>